-- India's State Government to Sell Its Stake in Punjab Alkalies & Chemicals
-- Suprotip Ghosh
-- 2010-07-15T01:44:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/india-s-state-government-to-sell-its-stake-in-punjab-alkalies-chemicals.html

          
          
             The government of the Indian state
of Punjab is planning to sell its entire 44.26 percent stake in
Punjab Alkalies & Chemicals, according to an ad in the Economic
Times.  
 The government holds the stake through the directorate of
disinvestment, according to the ad. IFCI Ltd. is the adviser to
the sale.  
